  "body": "I found a strange problem and confused me.\r\n\r\nI want to create a private network, the gensis file(my-gensis.json) is as follows:\r\n```\r\n{\r\n  \"config\": {\r\n        \"chainId\": 15,\r\n        \"homesteadBlock\": 0,\r\n        \"eip155Block\": 0,\r\n        \"eip158Block\": 0\r\n    },\r\n    \"coinbase\" : \"0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000\",\r\n    ......\r\n}\r\n```\r\nhere, the chainId is 15.\r\n\r\nFirst, I initialized successfully as follows:\r\n`./geth init my-gensis.json --datadir data`\r\n\r\nThen I tried to start the geth as follows:\r\n`./geth --rpc --rpcport 8545 --datadir data --port 30001 --rpcapi personal,db,eth,miner,net,web3 --networkid 100000 --nodiscover console`\r\n\r\nThe startup log is as follows:\r\n```\r\nWARN [03-19|15:56:35] No etherbase set and no accounts found as default \r\nINFO [03-19|15:56:35] Starting peer-to-peer node               instance=Geth/centos-dev-125-1/v1.7.3-stable/linux-amd64/go1.8.3\r\nINFO [03-19|15:56:35] Allocated cache and file handles         database=/home/work/.ethereum/geth/chaindata cache=128 handles=1024\r\n**INFO [03-19|15:56:35] Initialised chain configuration          config=\"{ChainID: 1 Homestead: 1150000 DAO: 1920000 DAOSupport: true EIP150: 2463000 EIP155: 2675000 EIP158: 2675000 Byzantium: 4370000 Engine: ethash}\"**\r\n```\r\nNote the bold context: ChainId is 1, not 15 defined in my gensis file! Other parameters were also inconsistent with the definition in the my-gensis.json file. It seemed that the private network connected to the public network?\r\n\r\nI checked over and over and was sure that the data dir, gensis file, command line were all ok. \r\n\r\nWho encountered this and resolved?\r\n\r\nThanks a lot.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
