    "body": "That looks very odd. Additionally, `database=/home/work/.ethereum/geth/chaindata` shows that it totally ignored your `--datadir`. \r\nRunning your comand locally, it works for me:\r\n```\r\n[user@work bin]$ ./geth --rpc --rpcport 8545 --datadir data --port 30001 --rpcapi personal,db,eth,miner,net,web3 --networkid 100000 --nodiscover console\r\nINFO [03-19|09:32:56] Maximum peer count                       ETH=25 LES=0 total=25\r\nINFO [03-19|09:32:56] Starting peer-to-peer node               instance=Geth/v1.8.3-unstable-6494f4e8/linux-amd64/go1.10\r\nINFO [03-19|09:32:56] Allocated cache and file handles         database=/home/user/go/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/build/bin/data/geth/chaindata cache=768 handles=512\r\n```\r\nCould you try with a more recent release and see if you get the same problem? ",
